[normal]Written evidence from Neil Cooper and Gerald Walther, Peace Studies, University of Bradford[bold]Data on Compliance Visits to Companies and Sites Holding Open Export Licences[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Abstract
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Context
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]‘we have reached the stage where the organisation is processing something like 17,000 standard individual export licences a year with resources adequate to slightly more than half that figure…if we could move only a small proportion of these over to open licensing, it would free up resources…to focus on the more difficult cases’.
[normal] 
